==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
A primary word, including the comparative (second form)

===Pronunciation===
νέος, νεώτερος / neos  neōteros / neh'-os, neh-o'-ter-os

===Adjective===
'''νέος'''

# “new”, that is, (of persons) youthful, or (of things) fresh; figuratively regenerate: [[new]], [[young]].

